-- Southwest Airlines to Increase Capacity in 2011 First Half as Demand Rises
-- B y   M a r y   S c h l a n g e n s t e i n
-- 2010-12-08T15:47:48Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-12-08/southwest-airlines-to-increase-capacity-in-2011-first-half-as-demand-rises.html
Southwest Airlines Co., the largest
low-fare carrier, will increase capacity in the first half of
2011 based on improving demand. Capacity will increase about 8
percent in the first quarter and 5 percent in the second, Chief
Financial Officer Laura Wright said today in New York.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Mary Schlangenstein in Dallas at 
